           <display>inscribed with the colophons and encomia of the artist and several other collaborators: Dai Xi, Luchuang Juren, Lun An, Meng Xin, Shun Qi, Shun Shi, Shun Si, Song Ping, Yu An, Jing Dong Juren, and Wen Jie</display>
           <inscription source="Owyoung, Steven D. 'CHINESE PAINTINGS.' Bulletin (St. Louis Art Museum) 17, no. 3 (1985): 1-31. P. 21.">
               <author refid="78529529" vocab="viaf">Dai Xi</author>
	       <position/>
               <text type="text">Wu [Chung-chün] Cheng-fang, fellow Inspector of Schools, visited Mount Yen-tang in my home region of Che to view the beauty of Lung-ch'iu. On his return, he entrusted me to do this painting and add poetic phrases.
Written at the capital in the 27th year [1847], ninth month of the Tao</text>
           </inscription>
