           <display>The title appears three times: the first as a paper label on the brocade mounting cover (baoshou) by Shao Zhang (d. 1954); second as five large Chinese characters at the beginning of the handscroll (ti) by Qi Junzao (1793–1866); and third as four characters on the painting by the artist Dai Xi (1801–1860).  Source: Description of the work based on the Categories for the Description of Works of Art</display>
